Fifth: There are four ways in which something may be said to oblige Conscience: 1⁰, The Express Command of God obliges it, of itself and by its proper force: 2⁰, Human Laws oblige it, not by their own force, but in virtue of the divine commandz 3⁰, Our own Promises and Vows oblige it, by our own election and act: 4⁰, The Fear of giving Offence obliges it, by'virtue of a collateral and accidental influence.
